 The proposed referendum should be about reducing the burden on Kenyans and not creating more positions in government, Mount Kenya MPs have said. They Jubilee will not opposed a referendum aimed at improving the lives of Kenyans and lowering the wage bill. The MPs include Beatrice Nkatha (Tharaka Nithi), Mugambi Rindikiri (Buuri) Mpuru Aburi (EALA), Kimani Ichungwa (Kikuyu), Patrick Munene (Chuka Igambang'ombe), Gitonga Murugara (Tharaka) and Kareke Mbiuki of Maara. "Raila should not dictate the referendum to be about what he wants. This should be about the 48 million Kenyans," Nkatha said. Ichungwa said referendum is not important if it the Constitution will be amended to create more positions in government. "If the referendum will reduce the wage bill and ease the burden of Kenyans, then we are ready. Raila should not give ultimatums because he does not own the country," Ichungwa said. Click here for the latest political news